    <item>
      <title>Geoje Panorama Cable Car — Nojasan Observatory</title>
      <link>https://kimpaper.github.io/en/posts/diary/2026-07-12-geoje-cablecar/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 12 Jul 2026 15:39:00 +0900</pubDate>
      <guid>https://kimpaper.github.io/en/posts/diary/2026-07-12-geoje-cablecar/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We rode the Geoje Panorama Cable Car (거제 파노라마 케이블카). It runs in one go from Hakdong Pass up to the summit of Nojasan (노자산), a mountain on Geoje Island off the southern coast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Mountain ridges seen from the observatory&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://kimpaper.github.io/images/2026-07-12-geoje-cablecar-1.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The moment you step off at the top, the ridges just keep folding into the distance. This is not a view you get around Seoul.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Rocky ridge and the archipelago&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://kimpaper.github.io/images/2026-07-12-geoje-cablecar-2.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
